problem_text: Symphony No. 9 is a music piece. Composers write music pieces. Beethoven wrote Symphony No. 9. Vienna Music Society premiered Symphony No. 9. Vienna Music Society is an orchestra. Beethoven leads the Vienna Music Society. Orchestras are led by conductors.
predicates:
MusicPiece(x) ::: x is a music piece.
Composer(x) ::: x is a composer.
Writes(x, y) ::: x writes y.
Orchestra(x) ::: x is an orchestra.
Premiere(x, y) ::: x premiered y.
Leads(x, y) ::: x leads y.
Conductor(x) ::: x is a conductor.

tests.questions: Based on the above information, is the following statement true or false? Beethoven is a conductor who leads an orchestra that premiered a music piece.
tests.conclusions: ∃x ∃y ∃z (Composer(x) ∧ Leads(x, y) ∧ Orchestra(y) ∧ MusicPiece(z) ∧ Writes(x, z) ∧ Premiere(y, z)) ::: Beethoven is a conductor who leads an orchestra that premiered a music piece. TRUE

tests.questions: Based on the above information, is the following statement true or false? Beethoven is a conductor and writes a music piece that was premiered by an orchestra.
tests.conclusions: ∃x ∃y ∃z (Composer(x) ∧ MusicPiece(y) ∧ Orchestra(z) ∧ Writes(x, y) ∧ Premiere(z, y) ∧ Leads(x, z) ∧ Conductor(x)) ::: Beethoven is a conductor and writes a music piece that was premiered by an orchestra. TRUE

tests.questions: Based on the above information, is the following statement true or false? Vienna Music Society is an orchestra that premiered a music piece written by Beethoven, and Beethoven leads the Vienna Music Society.
tests.conclusions: Orchestra(viennamusicsociety) ∧ Premiere(viennamusicsociety, symphonyno9) ∧ Writes(beethoven, symphonyno9) ∧ Leads(beethoven, viennamusicsociety) ::: Vienna Music Society is an orchestra that premiered a music piece written by Beethoven, and Beethoven leads the Vienna Music Society. TRUE

tests.questions: Based on the above information, is the following statement true or false? A conductor leads an orchestra that premiered a music piece written by a composer.
tests.conclusions: ∃x ∃y ∃z (Conductor(x) ∧ Orchestra(y) ∧ Premiere(y, z) ∧ Writes(composer, z) ∧ Composer(composer)) ::: A conductor leads an orchestra that premiered a music piece written by a composer. FALSE

tests.questions: Based on the above information, is the following statement true or false? Any conductor who leads an orchestra that premiered a music piece also writes that music piece.
tests.conclusions: ∀x ∀y ∀z (Conductor(x) ∧ Leads(x, y) ∧ Orchestra(y) ∧ Premiere(y, z) → Writes(x, z)) ::: FALSE

tests.questions: Based on the above information, is the following statement true or false? Beethoven leads an orchestra which premiered a music piece, and Beethoven is a composer who writes music pieces.
tests.conclusions: Leads(beethoven, viennamusicsociety) ∧ Composer(beethoven) ∧ Writes(beethoven, symphonyno9) ∧ Orchestra(viennamusicsociety) ∧ Premiere(viennamusicsociety, symphonyno9) ∧ MusicPiece(symphonyno9) ::: Beethoven leads an orchestra which premiered a music piece, and Beethoven is a composer who writes music pieces. TRUE

tests.questions: Based on the above information, is the following statement true or false? The Vienna Music Society, an orchestra, premiered Symphony No. 9, and Beethoven, a composer, wrote Symphony No. 9 and leads the Vienna Music Society.
tests.conclusions: (Orchestra(viennamusicsociety) ∧ Premiere(viennamusicsociety, symphonyno9)) ∧ (Composer(beethoven) ∧ Writes(beethoven, symphonyno9) ∧ Leads(beethoven, viennamusicsociety)) ::: TRUE

tests.questions: Based on the above information, is the following statement true or false? Beethoven is a conductor and writes music pieces, and the Vienna Music Society is an orchestra that premiered a music piece that Beethoven wrote.
tests.conclusions: ∃x ∃y (Conductor(x) ∧ Writes(x, y) ∧ MusicPiece(y) ∧ Orchestra(viennaMusicSociety) ∧ Premiere(viennaMusicSociety, y) ∧ Author(x, y)) ::: Beethoven is a conductor and writes music pieces, and the Vienna Music Society is an orchestra that premiered a music piece that Beethoven wrote. TRUE

tests.questions: Based on the above information, is the following statement true or false? Beethoven is a composer and leads an orchestra that premiered a music piece.
tests.conclusions: ∃x ∃y ∃z (Composer(x) ∧ Leads(x, y) ∧ Orchestra(y) ∧ Premiere(y, z) ∧ MusicPiece(z)) ::: TRUE

tests.questions: Based on the above information, is the following statement true or false? Any composer who writes a music piece is a conductor who leads an orchestra that premiered that music piece.
tests.conclusions: ∀x ∀y (Composer(x) ∧ Writes(x, y) → ∃z (Conductor(z) ∧ Leads(z, Orchestra) ∧ Premiere(Orchestra, y))) ::: FALSE
